abstract: SAN FRANCISCO, Cal., Aug. 20.--The Brit  ish ship Huntingtonshire was wrecked on Point Reys to-day, and 18 lives were lost. Point Reys is about 40 miles north of the Golden Gate, and is a rocky promontory jutting out into the Pacific from the western coast of Marin County. Owing to the lack of direct communication with the Point, only meagre details of the wreck have been received.

abstract: MILWAUKEE, Wis., Aug. 22.--The Canadian schooner Lilly Hamilton foundered in the lake and sank early yesterday morning. Capt.
